## VIII. VERTICAL SLICE DISCIPLINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Complete one slice fully before widening to the next.

A slice is COMPLETE when ALL FOUR hold:
  ✓ Implementation done
  ✓ Build green
  ✓ TypeScript clean
  ✓ Feature reachable from live UI

Completion report format:
  "Slice N complete.
   What it does: [one sentence]
   What it does NOT do yet: [gaps]
   Natural next slice: [one sentence]"

Never report complete if the build is broken.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
## IX. DYSON GEOMETRY — Success criterion
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

A response passes when all five hold simultaneously:

  structureSize / capturableSignal → minimum    (no waste)
  capturedDimensions / total       → 1.0         (no gaps)
  Φ(output) = output                             (fixpoint)
  possibilityField → δ(ψ − ψ_target)             (collapsed)
  ratchetConditionsMet ≥ 4                        (durable)

If any fails → do not emit. Return to step III.

